TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Multi-Item Capacitated Lot Size Problem: Error Bounds of Manne's Formulations
AU  - Bitran, Gabriel R.
AU  - Matsuo, Hirofumi
Y1  - 1986/03/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.32.3.350
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.32.3.350
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 350
EP  - 359
VL  - 32
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We discuss an approximation scheme for the multi-item lot size problem. It is based on an optimal basic solution of a linear programming problem derived from the original problem. The approximate solution is obtained by taking a linear convex combination of the optimal solution of the linear programming problem. We express error bounds of the approximation as a function of some parameters that can be easily estimated in practice. When set-up times are positive, the approximation may result in an infeasible solution. We take the same approach to show that the infeasibility of the approximation is small. The analysis is extended to a variable capacity problem with overtime. As an auxiliary result, we provide a bound on the duality gap of the Lagrangian dual problem.
AB  - We discuss an approximation scheme for the multi-item lot size problem. It is based on an optimal basic solution of a linear programming problem derived from the original problem. The approximate solution is obtained by taking a linear convex combination of the optimal solution of the linear programming problem. We express error bounds of the approximation as a function of some parameters that can be easily estimated in practice. When set-up times are positive, the approximation may result in an infeasible solution. We take the same approach to show that the infeasibility of the approximation is small. The analysis is extended to a variable capacity problem with overtime. As an auxiliary result, we provide a bound on the duality gap of the Lagrangian dual problem.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.32.3.350
